HEADWORD: Satinette
<hw>Sat`i*nette"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One of a breed of
fancy frilled pigeons allied to the owls and turbits, having the body
white, the shoulders tricolored, and the tail bluish black with a large
white spot on each feather.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Satin weave</ent>⟦br⟧
